---
// "Also works for…" fold divider — agent-memory-pivot WS-12, GLOBAL-036.
// The agent-memory band (above) is the home page's PRIMARY narrative; this
// quiet divider demotes the general-purpose persona content that follows it
// (the multi-surface CodePanel + the "eight boxes" Replaces strip — the P1
// solo-builder / P3 analyst / P4 backend-engineer framing) into a clearly
// SECONDARY fold. Nothing is deleted; the framing just stops competing with
// the wedge. Deliberately muted — no accent, no CTA, no JS — so it reads as a
// section break, not a second hero. The gated hero wordmark/lede are WS-13.
---

<section class="awf" aria-labelledby="awf-title">
  <p class="awf__kicker">Also works for</p>
  <h2 class="awf__title" id="awf-title">
    Solo builders, analysts, and backend engineers.
  </h2>
  <p class="awf__lede">
    Agent memory is the sharp edge &mdash; but the same talk-to-it database is
    a whole backend you didn&rsquo;t have to build. If you&rsquo;re shipping a
    side project, exploring data, or replacing a CRUD service, it works for you
    too.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .awf {
    max-width: 880px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(40px, 6vw, 72px) 24px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .awf__kicker {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
  }

  .awf__title {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.8vw, 28px);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.12;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    max-width: 28ch;
    color: var(--fg-dim);
  }

  .awf__lede {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: clamp(14px, 1.6vw, 16px);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
</style>
